<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2>EverQuest Producer Brad McQuaid posted the following to the alt.games.everquest newsgroup: <br><br>When an NPC has a ! in front of their name, that means he/she/it is essentially 'turned off' -- this could be for a variety of reasons: bad data, there was a problem with the NPC and we manually turned it off, it's placeholder until new data is put in, etc. <br></font></td></tr>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2><font color=#800000><a name=66></a><b><br>Brell Serilis and Guild Forms</b></font><font color=#006600 size=1> [ <a href=mailto:eq_trade@usa.net target=main><font color=#006600>ShadowMaster</font></a> at 08:55 CST ]</font></font></tr></td>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2>The following has been posted to the patch server. Included is the announcement of a new world server entitled Brell Serilis.<br> <br>We have just activated the Guild submission forms in the EverQuest login server. For more information regarding the new guild submission process, please go to &quot;Guilds&quot; located in the &quot;Players Guide&quot; section of the official EverQuest web page (www.everquest.com).<br> <br>In addition to activating the new guild submission form, we have brought up a new server, Brell Serilis. <br><br>- The EverQuest Team <br><br></font></td></tr>
