<table BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=100%>
<tr><td BGCOLOR=#800000><b><font face="Comic Sans MS" color=#FFFF00 size=2>&nbsp;19 July 1999, Monday</font></b></td></tr>
<tr><td><table BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=5 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=100%>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2><font color=#800000><a name=67></a><b><br>In Development...</b></font><font color=#006600 size=1> [ <a href=mailto:eq_trade@usa.net target=main><font color=#006600>ShadowMaster</font></a> at 13:39 CST ]</font></font></tr></td>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2>General Issues <br>- We are working on implementing a command which will allow players level 20 and above, to add a last name to their character with out the need of contacting a GM on-line. <br><br>- Functionality is being added to allow Enchanters to enchant items. <br><br>- We have been looking at ways to add the ability to rent and occupy real-estate in the world of Norrath. <br><br>- The ability to send messages to everyone in a players Friend's List whom are currently on-line. <br><br>- Adding the option for players to not allow looting before a guild war or duel is initiated. <br><br></font></td></tr>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2><font color=#800000><a name=68></a><b><br>Test Server Patch Message </b></font><font color=#006600 size=1> [ <a href=mailto:eq_trade@usa.net target=main><font color=#006600>ShadowMaster</font></a> at 13:37 CST ]</font></font></tr></td>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2>The following changes and game play enhancements have been made to the Test Server, <br><br>- The &quot;r&quot; key will now initiate the &quot;/tell&quot; command.<br><br>- The /surname command has been added, which allows a player of 20th level or greater to issue his or her character a last name.<br>- If a character is knocked unconscious, and has no stamina, the player will still regain consciousness.<br>- Players are no longer able to cast Shadowstep next to a zone point and teleport to an area past the teleport region, which is inaccessible to other characters.<br>- If a player is too far from a corpse while attempting to perform the /loot command, a message will now be given.<br>- If the user was under the effect of either Treeform or Minor Illusion, then had Spirit of Wolf cast on them, the player would be able to move in their altered state - This is no longer possible.<br>- If a character is blinded, the chat box will no longer flash.<br>- The Eye of Zomm now allows the caster to travel up and down.<br>- If a shuriken or throwing knife is equipped, then unequipped, the weapon will no longer remain on the character model.<br>- When player dispels minor illusion, the character's weapons will no longer disappear from the character model.<br>- Monk trainers will now train Instill Doubt. <br>- The EverQuest Team <br><br></font></td></tr>
</table></td></tr></table>
<table BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=100%>
<tr><td BGCOLOR=#800000><b><font face="Comic Sans MS" color=#FFFF00 size=2>&nbsp;17 July 1999, Saturday</font></b></td></tr>
<tr><td><table BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=5 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=100%>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2><font color=#800000><a name=69></a><b><br>New Producer Letter: New Zones</b></font><font color=#006600 size=1> [ <a href=mailto:eq_trade@usa.net target=main><font color=#006600>ShadowMaster</font></a> at 06:45 CST ]</font></font></tr></td>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2>A new <a href=http://everquest.station.sony.com/n_letter.html> Producer Letter </a> has been published by Brad McQuaid: <br><br>7/16/99 <br>Welcome Back! <br><br>First, I’d like to thank all of you who’ve been helping out on the Test Server – the testing of the PvP Teams code is coming along quite nicely. We’re probably looking at about another two weeks or so of the test server being configured that way, after which we will bring Tallon Zek online. <br><br>I wanted to talk a little about the upcoming zones we’re working on. The first of these new, free downloads will be the Temple of Solusek Ro, a smaller dungeon of sorts which will be rich in quests. The second will be Paineel, home of the Heretics, situated south of Toxullia Forest. Once this zone is online, Erudite Necromancers will start in their city. And finally, the Hole, which will be a mid to higher level dungeon underneath Paineel. I expect to see the first zone come online in a month or so, followed by a new zone every month or two after that. Oh, and one of the issues we’re debating is whether to make these zones patch automatically, or whether to make them optional downloads – let us know what you think. <br><br>Which brings me to the new Voting screen in the EverQuest front-end. How we will patch add-on zones is just one issue of many with which we can conduct a poll now. And we really do appreciate all of you taking the time to read through the questions and casting your vote. This is a great opportunity for all of you players to be heard, and it really helps us understand the feelings and opinions of our player base. <br><br>You may have noticed a Guild button appear suddenly in the front-end as well. Very soon we will be activating this new functionality which should allow for the maintenance and approval of Guilds on a more global basis – it should provide for quicker Guild approvals as well as making it easy to administer Guild related activities. And look for additional Guild functionality both in the front-end and in-game soon – we’ve only scratched the surface. <br><br>Before I close I wanted to give the Rogues an update. Make Poison is still underway and coming along quite nicely. We’ve also enhanced your class in some additional ways, and we encourage you to check it out on the Test Server. Backstab now has a minimum damage it can do, and we’ve also modified both Sneak and Hide such that you can move while hidden (albeit at Sneak speeds) and it also let’s Rogues know if their Sneak and Hide attempts were successful. <br><br>Oh, and it looks like there will be an EverQuest players get together at GenCon on Thursday (the first night) night – we’ll post more details soon, but it’s looking like we’re going to rent out a pizza place and we’ll be showing both the Expansion and Sovereign™ there as well. <br><br>See you next week, <br><br>–Brad <br><br></font></td></tr>
</table></td></tr></table>
<table BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=100%>
<tr><td BGCOLOR=#800000><b><font face="Comic Sans MS" color=#FFFF00 size=2>&nbsp;16 July 1999, Friday</font></b></td></tr>
<tr><td><table BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=5 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=100%>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2><font color=#800000><a name=70></a><b><br>EQ Network Problems</b></font><font color=#006600 size=1> [ <a href=mailto:eq_trade@usa.net target=main><font color=#006600>ShadowMaster</font></a> at 08:30 CST ]</font></font></tr></td>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2>Connection Problem Update 7/15/99 12:30 pm <br>The 4 severed OC-48 lines have been patched and all data flow over them has resumed. <br><br>- The EverQuest Team <br><br>Connection Problem 7/15/99 11:30 am <br><br>A total of 4 OC-48 fiber lines have been severed between Los Angeles and San Diego, which is resulting in a number of players being unable to connect to the EverQuest servers. The effected Internet Service Providers are aware of the problem and are in the process of rerouting customers. <br><br>- The EverQuest Team <br></font></td></tr>
</table></td></tr></table>
<table BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=100%>
<tr><td BGCOLOR=#800000><b><font face="Comic Sans MS" color=#FFFF00 size=2>&nbsp;13 July 1999, Tuesday</font></b></td></tr>
<tr><td><table BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=5 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=100%>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2><font color=#800000><a name=71></a><b><br>New Patch Msg.</b></font><font color=#006600 size=1> [ <a href=mailto:eq_trade@usa.net target=main><font color=#006600>ShadowMaster</font></a> at 02:44 CST ]</font></font></tr></td>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2>The Test Server will be down between the hours of 6pm and 6am PDT for internal testing purposes.  This schedule for the Test Server will only occur for approximately 1 week, after that the Test Server will remain on-line 24 hours a day.<br><br>UUnet will be performing maintenance at 3:00 AM, on July the 13th, which will result in players losing connection to the servers.  Since this maintenance will be taking place, we have moved our regularly scheduled update time from 7:00am to 3:00am for tomorrow only.  UUnet has given us an approximate downtime of 3 hours. A list of game play enhancements is listed below.<br><br>Root spells will now overwrite spells with both positive and negative movement components in a more consistent pattern.<br><br>Banish Undead and Banish Summoned (LVL 49 CLERIC, NECROMANCER, MAGICIAN, DRUID, etc.) have been changed from All or Nothing saving throws to a regular saving throws.  This will make them easier to use against high level creatures.<br><br>Magician summoning spells that produce multiple items have been changed to summon more items as the Magician's level increases.<br><br>All Poison and Disease DOT spells have received tuning.<br><br>Druid DOT's (stinging swarm series) has been adjusted to do more damage over a shorter period of time.<br><br>Immolate (DRUID) now does more damage, but has a shorter duration.<br><br>Mesmerization (ENCHANTER) has been changed to a straight AOE radius spell - it will no longer hang in the area.  The AOE radius has been increased, as has the range.<br><br>Ice (LVL 49 DRUID) has been changed from an AOE spell to a single target DD spell.<br><br>Rage (SHAMAN) has been upgraded to a LVL 49 spell - Fury remains level 34.<br><br>Invisibility spells (Invisibility, Gather Shadows, Camouflage, etc.) will now blink before they wears off.<br><br>Hitting F1 twice, or /pet target will now target your pet.The Duration on Pack Regeneration (DRUID) has been increased.<br><br>Shield of Lava (MAGICIAN) has had its mana cost reduced.<br><br>The Research entries for Intensify Death and Hungry Earth (NECROMANCER) have been updated.<br><br>New high level Necromancer spells have been added to vendors.<br><br>A new Wizard spell Chill Sight has been added to the Wizard vendors.<br><br>The Magician's Summon Heatstone and Summon Coldstone spells will now work as long as the Stone is held or worn (the spell effect will never wear off).<br><br>The Insight spell (ENCHANTER) now adds Wisdom, not Intelligence.  Brilliance still adds Intelligence.<br><br>The Tashan series (ENCHANTER) has had the recasting time reduced.<br><br>Research for higher level spells has been made a bit easier.<br><br>Spells that Add HP now work better on pets.<br><br>The Necromancer's replacement spell for Charm (Screaming Terror) is on the vendors.  Play with this spell - it is different from any other spell of this type that you have ever seen.<br><br>Shrink (SHAMAN) has been put in to the game.  It is a Level 19 spell, and available in all Shaman starting cities.  This spell will only be castable in dungeons.  It will not leave an icon on your screen - Shrink will last until you zone.<br><br>High level Bard song (LVL 40+) will be slightly easier to sing (less missed notes).<br><br>- The EverQuest Team</font></td></tr>
</table></td></tr></table>
